definitions.definition: A surname derived from the Old Norse given name Þorsteinn , brought to England by Vikings .
A male given name from the Germanic languages , occasional transferred use of the surname.
A village and civil parish in Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk , England ( OS grid ref TL9165 ) .
